snippet.textDisplay:
I'm deeply grateful to each and every one of you for showing love and support to our song, Harkalay. As co-lyricist and cultural consultant, it's an incredible feeling to see our work resonate with so many hearts.

Your enthusiasm and appreciation mean the world to us, and we're thrilled to have been able to share a piece of our culture and heritage with you through music. Thank you for embracing the spirit of Harkalay, which means 'welcome' in Pashto. You've made us feel seen, heard, and celebrated!
Love and respect for all ❤️❤️

snippet.textDisplay:
After listening to this amazing Pashto song by Harkaly, I was completly astonished by the pure beauty and love of Pashtoon culture. In the video, when I saw three elder women sitting on sofas with two Pushtoon girls on each side, all looking focused and connected to the camera, I realized how dedicated they were to their performance.
As I kept watching, I noticed a remarkable older man with bright white hair that added to his charm. His face showed the hardworking and beautiful spirit of the Pashtoons. After finishing the song, I couldn't stop thinking about it and wanted to watch it again and again.
I want to thank Coke Studio for their incredible work in both audio and video. Sending love, respect, and best wishes to the whole team from my city, Mardan, KPK.
snippet.textOriginal:

As I kept watching, I noticed a remarkable older man with bright white hair that added to his charm. His face showed the hardworking and beautiful spirit of the Pashtoons. After finishing the song, I couldn't stop thinking about it and wanted to watch it again and again.
